Dori nodded, &quot;I'll see to that patrol personally.&quot;  She once again turned and made for the door. Hoping that she would this time be more successful then before.<br>
Chiara decided that Doriana had learned her lesson, mostly. <br>
&quot;Good... but, that will take a day or two.  I'd like for you and Tristan to take it this evening.&quot; <br>
Expecting her order to be obeyed, Chiara turned her attention back to Rhiannon. <br>
&quot;I'd like for you to inform the hunt mistresses of the decision we've made once we're done here... I think you'll like them, Rhiannon.&quot;   <br>
Dori stopped short and turned back around after Chiara gave her orders, &quot;But...&quot;  she took a deep breath, &quot;I thought I was past having to do overnight patrols.  I have a...&quot; She motioned to her hut, &quot;Zoe, and well I don't like...&quot;  She stopped knowing she sounded rather childish but she was rather used to sleeping with Zoe and it being only a few days before her joining, she really hated not being with her intended.  She might be almost twenty seasons old, but she knew how to throw a royal fit when she needed to. <br>
Chiara looked up, raising a brow. <br>
&quot;I'm fully aware of the fact you'd rather be home with your fiancee.  Perhaps you should have been too, before running in here.  As for being 'past' doing overnight patrols, it's a job that needs to be done to protect your sisters.  No one, not even me, is above that Princess.&quot;   <br>
Dori muttered under her breath, &quot;Then why don't you spend the night out there.&quot;  Out loud she responded, &quot;Yes my Queen, my *sister* Tristin and I will take the overnight patrol.&quot;  Her sister was about to have the night from hell if Dori had anything to do about it. <br>
Chiara heard the muttered comment, but chose to ignore it for now since Doriana was no longer arguing with her.<br>
&quot;Good... Thank you.&quot;  The queen turned her attention back to Rhia. <br>
Rhia was smiling when Chiara looked over to her. She watched Doriana leave the Hall, and then turned back to the desk. &quot;You two are very much like family to each other, aren't you?&quot; She didn't wait for a reply. &quot;I mean, that's good, since her Aella passed, that she has someone to be family for her...You just reminded me of a mother and daughter there.&quot;<br>
Chiara gave Rhiannon a chagrined look.  &quot;Can you say it was more like older sister and younger?  I don't think Doriana and Zoe are planning to wait to have children and I am at least a decade from wanting to be a grandmother.&quot;  She prays Angie gives her that long...<br>
Rhia is immediately regrettful. &quot; I didn't mean to imply anything with regards to your age...I was only talking about the tone of your voice...&quot; <br>
Chiara, seeing how seriously Rhia has taken her comment, immediately softens her features. <br>
&quot;Our relationship has always been a bit complicated.  Her mother helped me a lot when I first became Queen... so we're very much like true sisters in that way.  But she's also been my student, and possible heir, so I do have a certain more maternal authority.&quot; <br>
Chiara gives a slight shrug.<br>
&quot;Now, with Aella's death, the responsibility for her training falls almost entirely to me.  Thank the gods she's an adult though... I can't imagine teaching a fourteen or fifteen year old.&quot;   <br>
Rhiannon nods, realizing she'd misinterpreted Chiara's words.<br>
&quot;I suppose it would get a little confusing that way.&quot;<br>
Rhia changes the subject, wanting to get her lessons over with quickly.<br>
&quot;Was there anything else you had to teach me today?&quot; <br>
Chiara runs over her mental list of subjects to cover, and finds one urgent. <br>
&quot;Yes...  Doriana and Zoe are to be married soon and as a queen you'll be helping to officiate.  I have a scroll around here somewhere that's something of a script...&quot;  Chiara begins to search. &quot;Where the Hades... Ah...&quot;  She finds the scroll and gives it a triumphant shake before handing it to Rhiannon.  &quot;Take half an hour or an hour and go over this, and keep track of any questions or parts you need clarified.  Then come back and we'll talk it over.&quot; <br>
Rhiannon unrolls the scroll and glances at it quickly, then rolls it back up, grinning.<br>
&quot;Finally, something I can get into.&quot;<br>
She taps the scroll on the desk twice as she gets up, grins at Chiara, then walks out the door to review the scroll in the sunshine. <br>
Chiara watches the young queen go, a bit curious as to Rhia's enthusiasm over Amazon weddings. She shrugs.  Rhia probably just loves weddings and love in general. <br>
Knowing the contacts she made with other Queens during her trip need to be maintained, Chiara pulls out a blank scroll and inks up her quill... <br>
Rhia returns, scroll in hand. She sits down in front of Chiara, and not waiting for the older Queen to look up even, begins speaking.<br>
&quot;This is so sweet. Very romantic. Very...Amazon.&quot; she giggles. &quot;I had thought there would be more references to blood and battles though. I do have a couple of questions.<br>
I am not familiar with Greek mythology. And I have never heard anything like this- that humans used to have four arms and two heads, and then were seperated and always seek to find their other half. This must be a very ancient ritual.&quot; <br>
Chiara gives a laugh at Rhiannon's enthusiasm.  &quot;I guess I don't need to ask if you're a romantic, do I?&quot;<br>
Rhiannon blushes slightly.<br>
&quot;And, yes, it is a very ancient story,&quot; Chiara continued.  &quot;That's why I trust there's a deeper truth to it.&quot; <br>
Feeling like she has said a bit too much, she redirects the discussion.  &quot;You thought there would be blood and battles?&quot; <br>
Rhiannon grins. &quot;Well, that is what the Amazons are most famous for. And even though I know now that that's not what we're ALL about, there is always some truth behind the rumors. We ARE predominantly warriors, after all. &quot; <br>
&quot;True enough... We do all at least learn to defend ourselves.&quot;  Chiara sighed.  &quot;I know Aella was looking forward to officiating at her daughter's wedding one day.  I'd have to talk it over with Doriana first, of course, but what would you think of adding some symbol of Aella's presence to the ceremony?&quot; <br>
The War Queen hadn't allowed herself to consider for long what the symbol should be, deciding it was more important it be meaningful for Dori than herself.<br>
&quot;I think that's perfect! I'm sure Doriana will love it.&quot;<br>
Rhia looked a little sad for a second, thinking about how Aella should have been here talking about Doriana's marriage instead of her.  <br>
Chiara's expression is sad as well, and that provides a certain moment of connection between the two Queens. <br>
&quot;I think she will, too... I just don't want to make that decision for her.&quot; <br>
The War Queen sighs.<br>
&quot;So, do you think you have a good grasp on your responsibilities in this ceremony?&quot;<br>
Rhia waves the scroll a little.<br>
&quot;It doesn't seem that difficult. I would have to memorize my part. Putting meaning to it won't be hard, I'm a sucker for romance.&quot;<br>
She smiles once again, imagining herself and Chiara at Dori and Zoe's marriage ceremony.  <br>
Baily straightened out her leathers and frowned at herself in the mirror... a skirt, damnit... she looked ridiculous. Self consciously she made her way to the counsel hut and back to Chiara's office, knocking on the door and peeking her head in. <br>
By now, Chiara recognized the knock. <br>
&quot;Baily, come in...&quot;  While she was pleased to see her partner for any reason, to have her present now seemed... fated.  Chiara stood when Baily entered the room, and greeted her with a chaste, but hardly sisterly, kiss.  &quot;Rhiannon and I were just discussing plans for Dori and Zoe's wedding.&quot;   <br>
She still felt self conscious in the skirt, and was glad Chiara didn't comment. She returned the kiss and put an arm loosely around her waist. &quot;When is the wedding to take place? I forget already...&quot; She smiled softly. &quot;And is there anything I can do to help?&quot; <br>
